721725f-a.title: Manhattan: Morningside Avenue - Cathedral Parkway
721725f-a.text:
Morningside Park: A set of two views forming a panorama of the
southerly portion of same which is bounded in these views by Cathedral
Parkway (foreground, not seen), Manhattan Ave. (right) and Morningside
DDrive (left). Forking off Manhattan Ave. at West 114th Street is
Horningside Ave. to continue the easterly boundary of the Park. Atop
the bluff at the left is the Cathedral of St. John (Protestant Episcopal)
in a skeletal state. North of sar e are the 8 story structures of St.
Luke's Hospital. The photographer's vantage point is the 110th Street
station of the Ninth Ave. Elevated line and is vicwing northwestward.
March 1906.
George L. Balgue.
CREDIT LINE IMPER.TIVE ON ALL RDPRODUCTIONS.

718118f-b.title: Manhattan: Cathedral Parkway - Manhattan Avenue
718118f-b.text:
Cathedral Parkway (W. 110th Srreet) at Manhattan Avenue, show-
ing details of the 9th Avenue 'El'' system and its station at this
point. The photographer's general direction is westward. The
tracks curve southward at Columbus Avenue, and tha Parkway continues
uphill towards Amsterdam Avenue and Broadway. Morningside Park is
on the right with the Protestant Cathedral of St. John just beyond.
Note the glimpse of St. Lukes Hospital over the station shedroof.
June 6, 1940
Views 1,2,3
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS

721719f-a.title: Manhattan: Morningside Drive - Cathedral Parkway
721719f-a.text:
Morningside Drive, between Cathedral Parkway and 113th Street, view
northwest from; the Ninth Avenue Elevated station. This shows the
choir school, the old part of the Cathedral of St. John the
Divine, with the new nave under construction, and St. Luke's
Hospital on the northern side of 112th Street.
October 25, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
